The paper deals with the problem of learning description logic ontologies, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of queries for learning also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the study of ontologies, which are commonly used in databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of learning different fragments of description logic, which could be relevant to computational complexity theory (cs.CR).
